    "Table 8 summarises the performance of the four new dictionary algorithms.",
    "WEASEL 2.0 is on average 4% more accurate than BOSS and improves balanced accuracy by almost the same amount.",
    "Kernel/Convolution classifiers use convolutions with kernels, which can be seen as subseries used to derive discriminatory features.",
    "Each kernel is convolved with a time series through a sliding dot product creating an activation map.",
    "Technically, each convolution creates a series to series transform from time series to the activation map (see Definition 6)."
